<Grid
  xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
  xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
<Grid.RowDefinitions>
        <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
        <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
        <RowDefinition Height="10"/>
        <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
        <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
        <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
        <RowDefinition Height="10"/>
        <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
        <RowDefinition Height="10"/>
        <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
    </Grid.RowDefinitions>
    <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
        <ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
        <ColumnDefinition Width="10"/>
        <ColumnDefinition Width="*"/>
        <ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
    </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
	<!--TextBlock Grid.Row="1" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Text="1985-8-18" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}"/-->
	<TextBlock Grid.Row="1" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" HorizontalAlignment="Left" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}">
		<Run Text="{Binding MissionStartTime.Year}"/>-<Run Text="{Binding MissionStartTime.Month, StringFormat={}{0:00}}"/>-<Run Text="{Binding MissionStartTime.Day, StringFormat={}{0:00}}"/>
	</TextBlock>
    <!--TextBlock Grid.Row="1" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" HorizontalAlignment="Right" Text="05:00Z (06:00L)" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}"/-->
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="1" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" HorizontalAlignment="Right" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}">
		<Run Text="{Binding MissionStartTime.Hour, StringFormat={}{0:00}}"/>:<Run Text="{Binding MissionStartTime.Minute, StringFormat={}{0:00}}"/>Z (<Run Text="{Binding MissionStartTimeLocal.Hour, StringFormat={}{0:00}}"/>:<Run Text="{Binding MissionStartTimeLocal.Minute, StringFormat={}{0:00}}"/>L)
	</TextBlock>
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="3" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" Text="From:"/>
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="3" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" Text="Commander US Fifth Fleet"/>
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="4" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" Text="To:"/>
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="4" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" Text="Commander of TF150"/>
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="5" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" Text="Info:"/>
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="5" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" Text="Commander US Pacific Fleet"/>
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="7" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" Text="SUBJ:"/>
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="7" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" Text="Mission Orders"/>
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="7" Grid.Column="4" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" Text="#0-144.142.143"/>
	    <!--
	<Image Grid.Row="1" Width="250" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" Grid.RowSpan="6" Stretch="Uniform" HorizontalAlignment="Center" VerticalAlignment="Center" Source="{Binding Assets[ts_banner]}"/>
	-->
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="9" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" TextWrapping="Wrap">
      1.  (S)    Tactical Situation:
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>
	<!--
	  Due to the recent attacks by Iran on merchant shipping passing in and out of the Persian Gulf, it has been decided to organize escorted convoys to protect maritime trade.
	-->
	
	The Islamic Republic of Iran has threated to close the Straits of Hormuz to shipping connected with the United States' interests and allies to obtain leverage on the global scale.
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>The United States intends to resist Iranian threats and demonstrate its ability to transit the Straights as allowed under International Law.
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>COMMIDEASTFOR is arranging for convoy escort of tankers through the Strait of Hormuz to and from the Gulf of Aden. TF150 is to escort the first group of merchants towards the Mīnā' al-Bakr Oil Terminal on the Iraqi coast.
      <LineBreak/>
	
	  <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>
      2.  (S) Primary Objective:
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>
	<!--
      You are to escort the three oil tankers past the Strait of Hormuz to the designated area.
	-->
      Pass through the Strait of Hormuz from the Gulf of Aden into the Persian Gulf while defending escorted merchants from threats posed by the Islamic Republic of Iran.
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>
      3.  (S) Threat Report:
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>
	<!--
      Intel believes only a small force of patrol craft have been sortied by Iran at this point. Your forces should be able to brush them aside with little effort.
	-->
	
	It is assessed as highly likely that IRIN and IRGCN Surface Units from Bandar Abbas will be deployed in the Strait of Hormuz. Units likely to be representative of IRIN and IRGCN force mixes. Expect significant numbers of FAC/FIAC with limited support from larger patrol vessels.
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>It is assessed as likely that limited airborne support will be avaible to IRIN and IRGCN units from both Fixed and Rotary Wing Assets. It is assesed as likely that a limited number of air launched AShMs may be availble to air units.
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>IRIN submarines are not anticipated to be a threat at this time. It is assessed as higly likely that the IRIN is attempting to procure midget submarines, but assessed as highly unlikely that any are able to be deployed at this time.
	
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>
	<!--
      4.  (S) Warning Yellow - Do not fire unless fired upon
	-->
      <LineBreak/>
      <LineBreak/>
	  <!--
      5.  (S) EMCON - Maintain radio silence until otherwise directed
	  -->
	  
	  (S) EMCON - Due to high likelyhood of AShMs EMCON state is unrestricted
	  
    </TextBlock>
</Grid>